---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Home">
  <main class="hero">
    <h1 class="name">Sofia Voumvourakis</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Hi! I’m Sofia, a government and data science student who often finds herself asking: <span class="accent-text">“To advance humanity, are we losing it?”</span> I am driven to build a future where technology governance is resilient and equitable. Beyond the screen, I’m creative at heart—dabbling in poetry and art—and curious in practice—exploring philosophy, psychology, and global perspectives.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    height: 60vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .name {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 10vw, 6rem);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .intro {
    max-width: 600px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-grey);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .accent-text {
    color: var(--muted-teal);
    font-weight: bold;
  }
</style>